<a name="TARGET_RhiControl__FILE">
<div class="pagetitle">RHI Display Controls </div>

<xxxmeta xxxname="jhid" value="idv.controls.rhicontrol">

<div class="pagesubtitle">Overview</div>

<meta name="TARGET_RhiControl__jhid" value="idv.controls.colorrhicontrol">
The RHI display appears in the main 3D window and as a 2D plot in its display

control. The control window contains two tabs. The first shows the RHI in 2D:

<div class="cimg"><img src="controls/level2/images/ColorRhiControlGui1.gif"  alt="images/ColorRhiControlGui1.gif" ></div>
The second shows settings to control the display:

<div class="cimg"><img src="controls/level2/images/ColorRhiControlGui2.gif"  alt="images/ColorRhiControlGui2.gif" ></div>
<p></p>

<div class="pagesubtitle">Properties</div>

<ul>

  <li><b>Location</b>

    <p> Shows the starting and ending latitude and longitude points of the RHI

      line.</p>

  </li>

    <p></p>

  <li><b>Station</b>

    <p> Shows the station location id, latitude, longitude, and altitude.</p>

  </li>

    <p></p>

  <li><b>Color Table</b>

    <p> The control has a color bar showing the active color table and the associated

      high and low data values in the units the display is made in. As the mouse

      pointer is moved over the color bar, the value at a particular color is

shown. Click on the color bar to start the <a href="#TARGET_ColorTableEditor__FILE">Color
      Table Editor</a>. Or click on the button that displays the name of the

      color table to show a popup menu that allows you to change the range, select

      other color tables, etc.</p></li>

    <p></p>

  <li><b>Selector Position:</b></li>

    <p>Use the slider to change the position of the selector in the main display.</p>

	<p></p>

